"'''Once Bitten'''" is a short comic in ''[[Star Wars Tales 12]]'' in which Obi-Wan Kenobi tells the tale of his and [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn's]] encounter with Aurra Sing.

==Plot summary==
[[File:Jinn_Aurra.jpg|thumb|left|150px|Qui-Gon Jinn duels Aurra Sing]]
[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] is in the cockpit of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], contemplating things while flying his ship towards [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]]. The aged [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] asks to come in and tells a story of his and [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn's]] encounter with the evil [[Aurra Sing/Legends|Aurra Sing]].

The [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] had received a distress call from [[Mana Veridi]], a fellow Jedi who had been sent to investigate a disturbance on [[Kwannot]], asking them for assistance. On arrival, Qui-Gon tells Obi-Wan to relax and let [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] guide them. Soon they encounter Mana, only for her to be [[Assassin/Legends|assassinated]] by Aurra Sing. Aurra then attacks Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan, mocking Obi-Wan for only being a [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] and claiming she is after his [[Jedi Master/Legends|master]]. Feeling the duo won't easily be beaten, she retreats, stealing Mana's lightsaber.

As Han expresses disbelief at the thought of two Jedi being matched by a mere assassin, Obi-Wan explains that Aurra was a defected Jedi. Shortly after his story, Obi-Wan explains his beliefs on the Force, and Han, as usual, discredits them.

